         <entry xml:id="diplon-dlgenr"
                xml:lang="en"
                type="mainEntry"
                prev="#disqarin-dlgenr"
                next="#diprosofon-dlgenr"
                source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma" opt="false">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">דיפלון</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">dyplwn</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">diplon</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="pos" opt="false">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen" opt="false">m.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
               <form type="variant" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">דופלון</orth>
                  <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">dwplwn</orth>
                  <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">duplon</pron>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="Ox1" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">דופלון</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="Ox2" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">ברופלין</orth>
               </form>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="diplon-dlgenr-1" opt="false">
               <usg type="domain" opt="false">properties/features</usg>
               <usg type="socioCultural" norm="borrowing" opt="false">code-switching</usg>
               <usg type="normativity" opt="false">ad-hoc usage</usg>
               <usg type="meaningType" opt="false">lit.</usg>
               <usg type="frequency" opt="false">hapax legomenon</usg>
               <usg type="geographic" opt="false">Coptic</usg>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>double</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>double age</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <usg opt="false">
                     <lang opt="false">Ancient Greek+</lang>
                  </usg>
                  <quote>διπλοῦν</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>
                     בא בימים, ר' יודן בשם ר' יהודה בר סימון בא בדיפלון, ר' ברכיה בשם ר' אבא [ר' ברכיה בשם ר' אבא. Ox 1 Ox 2 וחרינה אמר] בפילון מפולש לחיי העולם הבא.
         </quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">59,6</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">II 635: 3</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">פילון</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>
                        [And Abraham was old,] he entered the days. R. Yudan said in the name of R. Yahuda bar Simon: He entered a double age (“diplon”). R. Berakhyah in the name of R. Abbaʾ said: he entered the open gateway (“diplon”) leading to the life of the world to come.
            </quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note anchored="true">=
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq 103 (31b: 6)</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">דיופלין</term>)
         </note>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <etym type="borrowing" opt="false">
               <lbl opt="false">source language</lbl>
               <lang opt="false">Ancient Greek+</lang>
               <cit type="etymon" xml:lang="grc">
                  <xr type="related" opt="false">
                     <lbl opt="false">Cf. LSJ</lbl>
                     <ref target="http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/morph?l=diplo%2Fos&amp;la=greek&amp;can=diplo%2Fos0"
                          type="entry">διπλόος</ref>
                  </xr>
               </cit>
            </etym>
            <note anchored="true">
               Cf. also Lat. duplum. 
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">AC II 109-110</bibl> renders 1. Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">δίπυλον</term> 'a house with two gates'; 2. Lat. dies + Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">παλαιόν</term> 'old aged'.
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Levy I 401</bibl>: Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">δύο πόλιον</term> 'double old (man)', but cf.
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Fleischer I 442</bibl>: Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">δίπυλον</term>.
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Jastrow I 303</bibl>: <term xml:lang="jpa">דיפלין</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">dyplyn</term>
               <term xml:lang="rabbinic">diplin</term> m. pl. of Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">διπλός</term> “double (age)“. Cf. also
      <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דיפלה</ref>
            </note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                  <title>Krauss, LW II</title>
                  <citedRange>210a</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
         </entry>
